text.paragraph:
                         Body as a Whole – anaphylactic/anaphylactoid reactions, systemic lupus erythematosus;  


Digestive System- hepatotoxicity, pancreatitis, vomiting; Hemic and Lymphatic System- agranulocytosis, aplastic anemia, hemolytic anemia, leukopenia, neutropenia, pancytopenia, thrombocytopenia, and thrombotic thrombocytopenic purpura; Infections and Infestations – 


Clostridium difficile-associated diarrhea; 


Metabolism and Nutritional Disorders – hypomagnesemia; 


Musculoskeletal System – bone fracture, myositis; Skin and Appendages – severe dermatologic reactions including erythema multiforme, Stevens-Johnson syndrome, toxic epidermal necrolysis (some fatal), cutaneous lupus erythematosus; Special Senses -speech disorder; 


Urogenital System – interstitial nephritis, urinary retention.

